main event: Radar contact with a rapidly moving object over Truax Field, Wisconsin on July 25, 1965.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar flying at a speed of over one thousand knots at an altitude of one hundred thousand feet., The object lost radar contact after being tracked for a duration of 10 minutes., Analysis suggests the speed was too slow for a meteor but compatible with a high-performance aircraft., The report indicates no known air traffic in the area at the time of the sighting., There was no physical evidence available for further evaluation.
sighted object: a rapidly moving object detected on radar
witness description: observer from an Army Air Defense Missile Site
